This paper discusses the security and searchability of encrypted data, which falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also proposes a new mechanism for mapping natural language expressions into a word-vector space, which involves information retrieval (cs.IR) and database systems (cs.DB). The paper also mentions the use of data structures to improve search efficiency, which is related to computer networks and communications (cs.CC) and software engineering (cs.SE).
